name: State liability for data sets
text: [§27-44.1]  State liability for data sets.  Data sets shall be available for informational purposes only.  The State does not warrant the fitness of any data set for a particular purpose and shall not be liable for any deficiencies in the completeness or accuracy of any data set, except where the State's conduct would constitute gross negligence, wilful and wanton misconduct, or intentional misconduct. [L 2013, c 263, pt of §2]
